sh
# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch error ...' command
# Terminal functions that output error display commands
#
# Default value: "sh"
#   Must execute (not just display) to show error and exit
#   The _error1/2/3 functions output shell commands via generate_error()
#
# The error command is used by COMBINATOR functions to output vpn-switch
# error commands that will be executed by the batch interpreter. For example:
#   echo "\"$VPN_SWITCH_CONTEXT_SCRIPT\" error \"Config not found: $config\""
#
# This allows errors to be:
# 1. Inspectable - visible in dry-run/inspect mode
# 2. Properly propagated - exit code flows through pipeline
# 3. Compatible with xargs - works in batch combinator context
#
# Phase 1 Issue #002: Error handling architecture
